The paper deals with computer-based image analysis, specifically in the field of histopathology. This suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel deep learning approach, which involves attention mechanisms and a recurrent network, indicating that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of attention mechanisms also suggests that it may belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with classification, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR), making it a possible sub-category as well.
